  "description": [
    "Original Lamentof Margaret of Valois SUGGESTED BY A PASSAGE IN DUMAS RHINE MARGOT BY T JEFF SMITH JR Bearup my heart let not one throb Reveal the pangs that burn within Force not one tear drop to mine eyes Such weakness now were deeper sin Ill wreathe with smiles my pallid lips Twine ro s es in my yielding hair Peck with the jeweled robe my form Tinge well my cheekstheyre strangely fair Fear not my feelings burst the chain Where Pride once rivets fast the link The hell pent up breaks not the bounds Till Vengeance guides it to the brink They say tis pasthes dead no more Will grief avail or teardrop soothe And bid me quench the liquid fire And strive my frowning brow to smoothe My pride they saya Valois pride Should LoveRemorseall feeling drown The heart must chill the mind grow dark They boast no sway beneath the crown Twas crime to love one neath my rank To step beyond the Royal pale He was a subjectl a queen We both were Aumanboth were frail The forfeit tvvas God not man Alone our souls to judgecondemn And oh may they his vengeance rue Who dared"
